<se_def>*: I must tell you, there's a fearfully cold land at the other end of this tunnel. You can run into a blizzard at any time of year.

<se_def>*: If you've some business up there,
that's one thing.<page>*: But if you're just going out of curiosity,
I'd turn back if I were you.
Don't say I didn't warn you!
<se_def>*: Dear Goddess! I thought I'd had it!
<se_def>*: A huge dog just came bounding through here.

<se_def>*: It nearly sent me flying, I tell you!
And it was no ordinary dog, either!
Oh, no! Its eyes were burning red.

<se_def>*: And it was armed!
It had a bloody great stick in its mouth!
<se_def>*: The whole world's been thrown into panic because of the sky turning red, but look at me...

<se_def>*: I'm stuck out here all on my own!
I know I've got orders and everything, but
sometimes I wonder what on earth I'm doing.
<se_def>*: Oooh, it's so c-c-cold...

<se_def>*: Duty is duty, but it's enough to kill a man,
standing out here in the cold all the time.
<se_def>*: I think I'll stop by at Marta's place after my shift and ask her for some of that hot tea again.

<se_def>*: Duty is duty, but it's enough to kill a man, standing out here in the cold all the time.
<se_def>*: I think I'll stop by at Marta's place after my shift and ask her for some of that hot tea again.
<se_def>*: What!? Marta's dead!?

<se_def>*: So there'll be no more hot tea, then!?
That was just about the only thing I had to
look forward to after a hard day's work!

<se_def>*: I can't believe it.
I mean, Marta seemed to be in such good health.
<se_def>*: Just goes to show you never can tell. You never know when your number's going to be up.
